Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Kenya Airways; Zenith Bank of Nigeria

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-08-09T15:30:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-kenya-airways-zenith-bank-of-nigeria.html
Kenya ’s All-Share Index fell for a
third day, slumping 3.1 percent to 63.13 by the 3 p.m. close in
Nairobi, the lowest close since Feb. 26, 2010.  Mauritius’s SEMDEX Index weakened for a third day, falling
2.5 percent to 1,893.58 by the 1:30 p.m. close in Port Louis,
the lowest since Nov. 12. The Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share
Index retreated for a sixth consecutive day, declining 1.9
percent to 22,519.32 by the 2:30 p.m. close in Lagos, according
to an e-mailed statement from the exchange. The Ghana Stock
Exchange Composite Index advanced 0.5 percent to 1,182.41 by the
3 p.m. close in Accra.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan  Africa ,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Kenya Airways Ltd. (KNAL)  , sub-Saharan Africa’s third-
biggest airline, tumbled 2.5 shillings, or 7.7 percent, to
30 shillings, the lowest closing level since Nov. 23, 2009,
after agreeing with the workers union to increase salaries by
25 percent.  Zenith Bank Plc (ZENITHBA)  ,  Nigeria ’s biggest lender by
market value, fell for the third day, losing 64 kobo, or 5
percent, to 12.28 naira, the lowest price since Sept. 29, after
the central bank nationalized Afribank Plc, Bank PHB Plc and
Spring Bank Plc, and as speculation deepened that the global
economic recovery is faltering.  Guaranty Trust Bank Plc (GUARANTY)  , the second-biggest
lender, weakened 62 kobo, or 4.9 percent, to 11.97 naira, the
lowest close since Sept. 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
